{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901808055,"sessionID":"ses_28401709affeCiPSt6S1RdIOFK","part":{"id":"prt_d7bff0dda001IAc19dfFcAR5oQ","messageID":"msg_d7bfee8fa001V2AWbIo5rvbvMA","sessionID":"ses_28401709affeCiPSt6S1RdIOFK","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-14bbbd51650343f4844021ee9f7ecdef","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/test_spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/test_spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube 测试用例规范 (TDD Specification)\n2: \n3: 要求 AI 在实现业务代码时，同步完成以下测试用例，作为实现完成度的判定标准。\n4: \n5: ## 1. 核心控制器测试 (Workload Manager)\n6: - **TestCase-WM-001**: 验证 Sandbox 创建接口。输入合法 `AgentRuntime` 定义，预期返回 `200 OK` 及 `sessionId`。\n7: - **TestCase-WM-002**: 验证 Sandbox 幂等性。相同 `name` 连续调用两次，预期返回相同 `sessionId`。\n8: - **TestCase-WM-003**: 验证非法输入拦截。输入缺失 `podTemplate` 的请求，预期返回 `400 Bad Request`。\n9: \n10: ## 2. 路由与会话测试 (Router)\n11: - **TestCase-RT-001**: 验证 Auth 拦截。未携带 Bearer Token 请求 `/v1/execute`，预期返回 `401 Unauthorized`。\n12: - **TestCase-RT-002**: 验证会话路由。模拟 Redis 中存在会话，Router 成功将请求转发至后端（Mock 后端）。\n13: - **TestCase-RT-003**: 验证会话过期。模拟 Redis 中 Token 已失效，返回 `404 Not Found`。\n14: \n15: ## 3. 存储层测试 (Store)\n16: - **TestCase-ST-001**: Redis Set/Get 验证。成功存储并检索 `SessionInfo` 结构体。\n17: - **TestCase-ST-002**: 过期时间验证。验证 Key 携带正确的 TTL（默认 24h）。\n18: \n19: ## 4. 编码执行引擎测试 (PicoD)\n20: - **TestCase-PD-001**: Python 代码执行。发送 `print(\"hello\")`，预期 stdout 为 `hello\\n`，exitCode 为 0。\n21: - **TestCase-PD-002**: 错误处理。发送语法错误代码，预期 stderr 包含 `SyntaxError`。\n22: \n23: ## 5. Python SDK 测试\n24: - **TestCase-SDK-001**: 上下文管理器验证。使用 `with CodeInterpreterClient(...) as client:` 确保结束时自动调用 `close()`。\n25: - **TestCase-SDK-002**: 异常映射。服务端返回 500 时，SDK 抛出自定义 `AgentCubeError` 而非原始 HTTP 错误。\n26: \n27: ## 实施要求\n28: - **Go 代码**：必须位于对应的 `*_test.go` 中，可通过 `go test ./...` 运行。\n29: - **Python 代码**：必须位于 `tests/` 目录或 `test_*.py` 文件中，可通过 `pytest` 运行。\n\n(End of file - total 29 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube 测试用例规范 (TDD Specification)\n\n要求 AI 在实现业务代码时，同步完成以下测试用例，作为实现完成度的判定标准。\n\n## 1. 核心控制器测试 (Workload Manager)\n- **TestCase-WM-001**: 验证 Sandbox 创建接口。输入合法 `AgentRuntime` 定义，预期返回 `200 OK` 及 `sessionId`。\n- **TestCase-WM-002**: 验证 Sandbox 幂等性。相同 `name` 连续调用两次，预期返回相同 `sessionId`。\n- **TestCase-WM-003**: 验证非法输入拦截。输入缺失 `podTemplate` 的请求，预期返回 `400 Bad Request`。\n\n## 2. 路由与会话测试 (Router)\n- **TestCase-RT-001**: 验证 Auth 拦截。未携带 Bearer Token 请求 `/v1/execute`，预期返回 `401 Unauthorized`。\n- **TestCase-RT-002**: 验证会话路由。模拟 Redis 中存在会话，Router 成功将请求转发至后端（Mock 后端）。\n- **TestCase-RT-003**: 验证会话过期。模拟 Redis 中 Token 已失效，返回 `404 Not Found`。\n\n## 3. 存储层测试 (Store)\n- **TestCase-ST-001**: Redis Set/Get 验证。成功存储并检索 `SessionInfo` 结构体。\n- **TestCase-ST-002**: 过期时间验证。验证 Key 携带正确的 TTL（默认 24h）。\n\n## 4. 编码执行引擎测试 (PicoD)\n- **TestCase-PD-001**: Python 代码执行。发送 `print(\"hello\")`，预期 stdout 为 `hello\\n`，exitCode 为 0。","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/test_spec.md","time":{"start":1775901808042,"end":1775901808054}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901808057,"sessionID":"ses_28401709affeCiPSt6S1RdIOFK","part":{"id":"prt_d7bff1188001wDYrOlTpQdnVnz","messageID":"msg_d7bfee8fa001V2AWbIo5rvbvMA","sessionID":"ses_28401709affeCiPSt6S1RdIOFK","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f67b8e37b6294e0f96f978f4e5108ecd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-036 — Dify 插件集成\n2: \n3: **Module:** integrations  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: Integrate AgentCube's code interpreter capabilities into Dify's plugin ecosystem, enabling Dify users to leverage AgentCube's sandboxed code execution environment directly within their AI workflows. This integration provides:\n12: \n13: 1. **Seamless Dify Integration** — A Dify-compatible plugin that exposes AgentCube's Code Interpreter as a tool callable from Dify agent workflows\n14: 2. **Reference Implementation** — A PCAP analyzer example demonstrating real-world usage of AgentCube SDK with LangChain/LangGraph agents in Kubernetes\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## Scope\n19: \n20: ### In Scope\n21: \n22: #### Dify Plugin Package (`integrations/dify-plugin/`)\n23: \n24: | Component | Description |\n25: |-----------|-------------|\n26: | `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest with metadata, resource permissions, and runner configuration |\n27: | `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider descriptor with identity and tool list |\n28: | `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` with credential validation |\n29: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema (router_url, workload_manager_url, language, code, command, session controls) |\n30: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` implementation delegating to AgentCube SDK |\n31: | `main.py` | Plugin entrypoint running `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n32: | `requirements.txt` | Dependency pins: `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`, `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10` |\n33: | Documentation | `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` |\n34: \n35: #### PCAP Analyzer Example (`example/pcap-analyzer/`)\n36: \n37: | Component | Description |\n38: |-----------|-------------|\n39: | `pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI service with LangChain/LangGraph agents for PCAP analysis |\n40: | `Dockerfile` | Container image using `uv` with vendored `agentcube` SDK |\n41: | `deployment.yaml` | Kubernetes Deployment with secrets and resource limits |\n42: | `requirements.txt` | FastAPI, LangChain stack, AgentCube dependencies |\n43: \n44: #### Python SDK Dependencies\n45: \n46: The integration depends on the existing `agentcube-sdk` providing:\n47: - `CodeInterpreterClient` — Session management and code execution via Control Plane + Router\n48: - `AgentRuntimeClient` — Agent runtime invocation\n49: - Exception hierarchy (`AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`)\n50: \n51: ### Out of Scope\n52: \n53: - Modifications to the AgentCube control plane or router\n54: - New AgentCube SDK features (uses existing SDK `>=0.0.10`)\n55: - Dify platform changes (integrates with existing Dify plugin framework)\n56: - OAuth authentication flows (commented out in provider, not required for MVP)\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## Impact Analysis\n61: \n62: ### User Impact\n63: \n64: | User Type | Impact |\n65: |-----------|--------|\n66: | Dify Users | Gain access to AgentCube's sandboxed code execution without leaving Dify workflows. Can execute Python/JavaScript/TypeScript code, run shell commands, and manage sessions. |\n67: | Platform Operators | Single deployment artifact (Dify plugin package) to install. PCAP analyzer example provides reference for building custom AgentCube-powered agents. |\n68: | Developers | Clear API surface via tool parameters. SDK handles session lifecycle, retry logic, and error propagation. |\n69: \n70: ### Technical Impact\n71: \n72: | Area | Impact |\n73: |------|--------|\n74: | **Architecture** | Adds a thin adapter layer between Dify's plugin interface and AgentCube SDK. No changes to AgentCube core. |\n75: | **Dependencies** | `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` (Dify framework), `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10` (AgentCube client) |\n76: | **Deployment** | Plugin packaged as Dify-compatible bundle; PCAP analyzer deployed as K8s workload |\n77: | **Testing** | Unit tests for tool/provider classes; integration tests against mock AgentCube endpoints |\n78: | **Security** | Credentials validated at provider level; sessions isolated per `session_id`; Router handles JWT auth |\n79: \n80: ### Risk Assessment\n81: \n82: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n83: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n84: | Dify plugin API changes | Medium | High | Pin `dify-plugin` to `<0.5.0`; monitor upstream releases |\n85: | AgentCube SDK breaking changes | Low | High | Pin `agentcube-sdk` version; SDK has stable public API |\n86: | Session leak in long-running workflows | Medium | Medium | Context manager ensures cleanup; explicit `stop()` on exit |\n87: | Timeout during long code execution | Medium | Low | Configurable per-call timeout; default 120s; PicoD timeout handling |\n88: \n89: ### Backward Compatibility\n90: \n91: - **No breaking changes** to existing AgentCube SDK\n92: - Plugin uses existing `CodeInterpreterClient` API surface\n93: - PCAP analyzer is a new example, no existing users affected\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ## Alternatives Considered\n98: \n99: ### Alternative 1: Direct API Integration (No Plugin)\n100: \n101: **Description:** Dify users call AgentCube Router endpoints directly via custom HTTP tool.\n102: \n103: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n104: |--------|------------|\n105: | Pros | No plugin development overhead; maximum flexibility |\n106: | Cons | Users handle session lifecycle manually; no credential management; no schema validation |\n107: | Verdict | ❌ Rejected — Poor UX; shifts complexity to end users |\n108: \n109: ### Alternative 2: LangChain Tool Wrapper\n110: \n111: **Description:** Build a LangChain tool instead of Dify plugin, usable in LangChain-based Dify agents.\n112: \n113: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n114: |--------|------------|\n115: | Pros | Broader LangChain ecosystem support; already used in PCAP analyzer |\n116: | Cons | Dify-native plugins have better integration (UI configuration, credential management); LangChain tool requires custom agent setup |\n117: | Verdict | ⚠️ Partial — Include as secondary option; Dify plugin is primary interface |\n118: \n119: ### Alternative 3: Multiple Tools (Execute, Upload, Download)\n120: \n121: **Description:** Split code interpreter into separate tools: `execute_code`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`.\n122: \n123: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n124: |--------|------------|\n125: | Pros | Finer-grained control in Dify workflows; simpler per-tool schema |\n126: | Cons | Session management across tools is complex; Dify tool selection overhead for simple use cases |\n127: | Verdict | ❌ Rejected — Single unified tool with optional parameters is more ergonomic |\n128: \n129: ### Alternative 4: Stateless Execution (No Session Reuse)\n130: \n131: **Description:** Each tool invocation creates a fresh sandbox, executes, and destroys it.\n132: \n133: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n134: |--------|------------|\n135: | Pros | Simpler mental model; no session state |\n136: | Cons | No persistent file system; higher latency per call; wasteful sandbox creation |\n137: | Verdict | ❌ Rejected — Session reuse is a key AgentCube feature; users can disable via `session_reuse=False` |\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## Implementation Phases\n142: \n143: ### Phase 1: Core Plugin (MVP)\n144: \n145: - Implement plugin manifest, provider, and tool YAMLs\n146: - Implement `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider._validate_credentials`\n147: - Implement `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool.execute` with code/command execution\n148: - Add unit tests with mocked SDK\n149: - Write `README.md` and `GUIDE.md`\n150: \n151: ### Phase 2: Session Management\n152: \n153: - Implement `session_id` and `session_reuse` logic\n154: - Add integration tests against real AgentCube endpoints (optional CI flag)\n155: - Handle edge cases: session creation failure, timeout, cleanup\n156: \n157: ### Phase 3: PCAP Analyzer Example\n158: \n159: - Validate `pcap_analyzer.py` against AgentCube deployment\n160: - Update `Dockerfile` and `deployment.yaml` for production readiness\n161: - Add end-to-end test with sample PCAP file\n162: \n163: ### Phase 4: Documentation & Polish\n164: \n165: - Complete `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore`\n166: - Add troubleshooting guide for common errors\n167: - Performance benchmark and timeout tuning\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## Success Criteria\n172: \n173: 1. **Functional** — Dify users can configure and invoke AgentCube Code Interpreter tool from workflows\n174: 2. **Reliable** — Session cleanup occurs on context exit; no leaked sandbox resources\n175: 3. **Observable** — Errors surface as `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` or `ToolInvokeMessage` JSON with actionable messages\n176: 4. **Documented** — Plugin includes multilingual labels (en_US, ja_JP, zh_Hans, pt_BR) and comprehensive README\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ## Dependencies\n181: \n182: | Dependency | Version Constraint | Source |\n183: |------------|-------------------|--------|\n184: | `dify-plugin` | `>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` | PyPI |\n185: | `agentcube-sdk` | `>=0.0.10` | AgentCube monorepo |\n186: | `requests` | (via agentcube-sdk) | PyPI |\n187: | `PyJWT` | `>=2.0.0` (via agentcube-sdk) | PyPI |\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ## References\n192: \n193: - `integrations/design.md` — Detailed file maps and code structures\n194: - `integrations/spec.md` — Formal requirements and scenarios\n195: - `python-sdk/design.md` — AgentCube SDK architecture\n196: - `python-sdk/spec.md` — SDK API contracts\n\n(End of file - total 196 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-036 — Dify 插件集成\n\n**Module:** integrations  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nIntegrate AgentCube's code interpreter capabilities into Dify's plugin ecosystem, enabling Dify users to leverage AgentCube's sandboxed code execution environment directly within their AI workflows. This integration provides:\n\n1. **Seamless Dify Integration** — A Dify-compatible plugin that exposes AgentCube's Code Interpreter as a tool callable from Dify agent workflows\n2. **Reference Implementation** — A PCAP analyzer example demonstrating real-world usage of AgentCube SDK with LangChain/LangGraph agents in Kubernetes\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775901808045,"end":1775901808056}}}}
