{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901841014,"sessionID":"ses_28401709affeCiPSt6S1RdIOFK","part":{"id":"prt_d7bff92e500157js9F3iEQIXZm","messageID":"msg_d7bff613f001A9hldHR5Fy28WV","sessionID":"ses_28401709affeCiPSt6S1RdIOFK","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-027e3ea25bf64b5a94b5ee8e96cf6c22","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/idle-cleanup/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/idle-cleanup/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Idle Cleanup — Design\n2: \n3: ## Module\n4: \n5: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see root `go.mod` in sandbox-orchestration design).\n6: \n7: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd`\n8: \n9: ### Time threshold\n10: \n11: ```go\n12: var SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n13: ```\n14: \n15: Idle expiration: `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`; delete when `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`.\n16: \n17: ### Annotation key\n18: \n19: The reconciler uses the same key as workload manager pod annotation for idle timeout tracking on the **Sandbox** object:\n20: \n21: - Import: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager`\n22: - Key: `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` = **`\"last-activity-time\"`**\n23: \n24: (Workload manager also sets `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout` on Sandbox metadata for template-driven idle configuration; **agentd** only reads `last-activity-time`.)\n25: \n26: ### Reconciler\n27: \n28: ```go\n29: package agentd\n30: \n31: type Reconciler struct {\n32:     client.Client\n33:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n34: }\n35: \n36: func (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n37: ```\n38: \n39: **Algorithm (exact behavior):**\n40: \n41: 1. `sandbox := &sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}`; `Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)`.\n42: 2. If `errors.IsNotFound(err)` → `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`.\n43: 3. If other get error → return `ctrl.Result{}, err`.\n44: 4. `lastActivityStr, exists := sandbox.Annotations[workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey]`.\n45: 5. If `exists && lastActivityStr != \"\"`:\n46:    - `lastActivity, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)`\n47:    - If parse err → `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30 * time.Second}, err`\n48:    - `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`\n49:    - If `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`:\n50:      - `r.Delete(ctx, sandbox)`; if err and not `IsNotFound` → `return ctrl.Result{}, err`\n51:    - Else:\n52:      - `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)}, nil`\n53: 6. `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`\n54: \n55: ### SetupWithManager\n56: \n57: ```go\n58: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n59:     return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n60:         For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n61:         Complete(r)\n62: }\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ## Binary `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n66: \n67: ### Scheme registration\n68: \n69: ```go\n70: var schemeBuilder = runtime.NewScheme()\n71: \n72: func init() {\n73:     utilruntime.Must(scheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n74:     utilruntime.Must(sandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n75: }\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ### Controller-runtime manager\n79: \n80: ```go\n81: mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{\n82:     Scheme:                 schemeBuilder,\n83:     Metrics:                metricsserver.Options{BindAddress: \"0\"},\n84:     HealthProbeBindAddress:   \"0\",\n85: })\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ### Controller registration (duplicate of SetupWithManager pattern)\n89: \n90: ```go\n91: err = ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n92:     For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n93:     Complete(&agentd.Reconciler{\n94:         Client: mgr.GetClient(),\n95:         Scheme: mgr.GetScheme(),\n96:     })\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ### Run\n100: \n101: ```go\n102: mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ## Watched resources\n106: \n107: | API group | Version | Kind | Trigger |\n108: |-----------|---------|------|---------|\n109: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `v1alpha1` | `Sandbox` | Default `For()` watch — creates, updates, deletes (per controller-runtime) |\n110: \n111: No explicit `Owns` or `Watches` — single primary resource `Sandbox`.\n112: \n113: ## Related workload-manager constants (context)\n114: \n115: From `pkg/workloadmanager` (not used by agentd reconcile logic but set when sandboxes are created):\n116: \n117: - `IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"` — duration string on Sandbox CR.\n118: - `LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"` — **read by agentd** for idle cleanup.\n119: \n120: ## Dependencies\n121: \n122: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors`\n123: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime`\n124: - `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`\n125: - `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime`\n126: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` (annotation key only)\n\n(End of file - total 126 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Idle Cleanup — Design\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see root `go.mod` in sandbox-orchestration design).\n\n## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd`\n\n### Time threshold\n\n```go\nvar SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n```\n\nIdle expiration: `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`; delete when `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`.\n\n### Annotation key\n\nThe reconciler uses the same key as workload manager pod annotation for idle timeout tracking on the **Sandbox** object:\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/idle-cleanup/design.md","time":{"start":1775901841004,"end":1775901841013}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901841018,"sessionID":"ses_28401709affeCiPSt6S1RdIOFK","part":{"id":"prt_d7bff96220017gyR0YRtNsdleG","messageID":"msg_d7bff613f001A9hldHR5Fy28WV","sessionID":"ses_28401709affeCiPSt6S1RdIOFK","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-80bee94c602749be971ae8cf40f581dd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"encoding/json\"\n6: \t\"net\"\n7: \t\"net/http\"\n8: \t\"net/http/httptest\"\n9: \t\"sync\"\n10: \t\"testing\"\n11: \t\"time\"\n12: )\n13: \n14: type integrationTestLogger struct {\n15: \tmu     sync.Mutex\n16: \tinfos  []string\n17: \terrors []string\n18: }\n19: \n20: func (l *integrationTestLogger) Info(msg string, args ...any) {\n21: \tl.mu.Lock()\n22: \tdefer l.mu.Unlock()\n23: \tl.infos = append(l.infos, msg)\n24: }\n25: \n26: func (l *integrationTestLogger) Error(msg string, args ...any) {\n27: \tl.mu.Lock()\n28: \tdefer l.mu.Unlock()\n29: \tl.errors = append(l.errors, msg)\n30: }\n31: \n32: type integrationHealthChecker struct {\n33: \tready bool\n34: }\n35: \n36: func (c *integrationHealthChecker) IsHealthy() bool { return true }\n37: func (c *integrationHealthChecker) IsReady() bool   { return c.ready }\n38: \n39: func TestE2EHealthz(t *testing.T) {\n40: \tlistener, err := net.Listen(\"tcp\", \"127.0.0.1:0\")\n41: \tif err != nil {\n42: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"failed to get free port: %v\", err)\n43: \t}\n44: \taddr := listener.Addr().String()\n45: \tlistener.Close()\n46: \n47: \tcfg := Config{\n48: \t\tAddr:            addr,\n49: \t\tReadTimeout:     5 * time.Second,\n50: \t\tWriteTimeout:    5 * time.Second,\n51: \t\tIdleTimeout:     60 * time.Second,\n52: \t\tShutdownTimeout: 5 * time.Second,\n53: \t}\n54: \tlogger := &integrationTestLogger{}\n55: \ts := NewHTTPServer(cfg, logger)\n56: \n57: \ts.router.Get(\"/healthz\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n58: \t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n59: \t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n60: \t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n61: \t})\n62: \n63: \terrCh := s.Start()\n64: \n65: \ttime.Sleep(50 * time.Millisecond)\n66: \n67: \tclient := &http.Client{Timeout: 2 * time.Second}\n68: \n69: \tresp, err := client.Get(\"http://\" + addr + \"/healthz\")\n70: \tif err != nil {\n71: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"failed to connect to server: %v\", err)\n72: \t}\n73: \tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n74: \n75: \tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n76: \t\tt.Errorf(\"expected status %d, got %d\", http.StatusOK, resp.StatusCode)\n77: \t}\n78: \n79: \tvar body map[string]string\n80: \tif decodeErr := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&body); decodeErr != nil {\n81: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"failed to decode response: %v\", decodeErr)\n82: \t}\n83: \tif body[\"status\"] != \"ok\" {\n84: \t\tt.Errorf(\"expected status %s, got %s\", \"ok\", body[\"status\"])\n85: \t}\n86: \n87: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 5*time.Second)\n88: \tdefer cancel()\n89: \ts.Stop(ctx)\n90: \n91: \tselect {\n92: \tcase <-errCh:\n93: \tcase <-time.After(1 * time.Second):\n94: \t}\n95: }\n96: \n97: func TestE2EReadyz(t *testing.T) {\n98: \tlistener, err := net.Listen(\"tcp\", \"127.0.0.1:0\")\n99: \tif err != nil {\n100: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"failed to get free port: %v\", err)\n101: \t}\n102: \taddr := listener.Addr().String()\n103: \tlistener.Close()\n104: \n105: \tcfg := Config{\n106: \t\tAddr:            addr,\n107: \t\tReadTimeout:     5 * time.Second,\n108: \t\tWriteTimeout:    5 * time.Second,\n109: \t\tIdleTimeout:     60 * time.Second,\n110: \t\tShutdownTimeout: 5 * time.Second,\n111: \t}\n112: \tlogger := &integrationTestLogger{}\n113: \ts := NewHTTPServer(cfg, logger)\n114: \n115: \tchecker := &integrationHealthChecker{ready: true}\n116: \ts.router.Get(\"/readyz\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n117: \t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n118: \t\tif checker == nil || !checker.IsReady() {\n119: \t\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n120: \t\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"not ready\"})\n121: \t\t\treturn\n122: \t\t}\n123: \t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n124: \t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ready\"})\n125: \t})\n126: \n127: \terrCh := s.Start()\n128: \n129: \ttime.Sleep(50 * time.Millisecond)\n130: \n131: \tclient := &http.Client{Timeout: 2 * time.Second}\n132: \n133: \tresp, err := client.Get(\"http://\" + addr + \"/readyz\")\n134: \tif err != nil {\n135: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"failed to connect to server: %v\", err)\n136: \t}\n137: \tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n138: \n139: \tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n140: \t\tt.Errorf(\"expected status %d, got %d\", http.StatusOK, resp.StatusCode)\n141: \t}\n142: \n143: \tvar body map[string]string\n144: \tif decodeErr := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&body); decodeErr != nil {\n145: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"failed to decode response: %v\", decodeErr)\n146: \t}\n147: \tif body[\"status\"] != \"ready\" {\n148: \t\tt.Errorf(\"expected status %s, got %s\", \"ready\", body[\"status\"])\n149: \t}\n150: \n151: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 5*time.Second)\n152: \tdefer cancel()\n153: \ts.Stop(ctx)\n154: \n155: \tselect {\n156: \tcase <-errCh:\n157: \tcase <-time.After(1 * time.Second):\n158: \t}\n159: }\n160: \n161: func TestMiddlewareChain(t *testing.T) {\n162: \tlogger := &integrationTestLogger{}\n163: \n164: \trouter := NewRouter()\n165: \n166: \trouter.Use(func(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n167: \t\treturn http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n168: \t\t\tdefer func() {\n169: \t\t\t\tif err := recover(); err != nil {\n170: \t\t\t\t\tlogger.Error(\"panic recovered\", \"error\", err)\n171: \t\t\t\t\thttp.Error(w, \"Internal Server Error\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n172: \t\t\t\t}\n173: \t\t\t}()\n174: \t\t\tnext.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n175: \t\t})\n176: \t})\n177: \n178: \trouter.Use(func(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n179: \t\treturn http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n180: \t\t\tlogger.Info(\"request\", \"method\", r.Method, \"path\", r.URL.Path)\n181: \t\t\tnext.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n182: \t\t})\n183: \t})\n184: \n185: \trouter.Get(\"/test\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n186: \t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n187: \t\tw.Write([]byte(\"test\"))\n188: \t})\n189: \n190: \treq := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/test\", nil)\n191: \tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n192: \n193: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n194: \n195: \tif w.Code != http.StatusOK {\n196: \t\tt.Errorf(\"expected status %d, got %d\", http.StatusOK, w.Code)\n197: \t}\n198: \n199: \tlogger.mu.Lock()\n200: \tdefer logger.mu.Unlock()\n201: \tif len(logger.infos) != 1 {\n202: \t\tt.Errorf(\"expected 1 info log, got %d\", len(logger.infos))\n203: \t}\n204: }\n205: \n206: func TestE2EPanicRecovery(t *testing.T) {\n207: \tlistener, err := net.Listen(\"tcp\", \"127.0.0.1:0\")\n208: \tif err != nil {\n209: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"failed to get free port: %v\", err)\n210: \t}\n211: \taddr := listener.Addr().String()\n212: \tlistener.Close()\n213: \n214: \tcfg := Config{\n215: \t\tAddr:            addr,\n216: \t\tReadTimeout:     5 * time.Second,\n217: \t\tWriteTimeout:    5 * time.Second,\n218: \t\tIdleTimeout:     60 * time.Second,\n219: \t\tShutdownTimeout: 5 * time.Second,\n220: \t}\n221: \tlogger := &integrationTestLogger{}\n222: \ts := NewHTTPServer(cfg, logger)\n223: \n224: \ts.router.Use(func(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n225: \t\treturn http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n226: \t\t\tdefer func() {\n227: \t\t\t\tif err := recover(); err != nil {\n228: \t\t\t\t\tlogger.Error(\"panic recovered\", \"error\", err)\n229: \t\t\t\t\thttp.Error(w, \"Internal Server Error\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n230: \t\t\t\t}\n231: \t\t\t}()\n232: \t\t\tnext.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n233: \t\t})\n234: \t})\n235: \n236: \ts.router.Get(\"/panic\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n237: \t\tpanic(\"intentional panic for test\")\n238: \t})\n239: \n240: \terrCh := s.Start()\n241: \n242: \ttime.Sleep(50 * time.Millisecond)\n243: \n244: \tclient := &http.Client{Timeout: 2 * time.Second}\n245: \n246: \tresp, err := client.Get(\"http://\" + addr + \"/panic\")\n247: \tif err != nil {\n248: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"failed to connect to server: %v\", err)\n249: \t}\n250: \tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n251: \n252: \tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusInternalServerError {\n253: \t\tt.Errorf(\"expected status %d, got %d\", http.StatusInternalServerError, resp.StatusCode)\n254: \t}\n255: \n256: \tlogger.mu.Lock()\n257: \tdefer logger.mu.Unlock()\n258: \tif len(logger.errors) != 1 {\n259: \t\tt.Errorf(\"expected 1 error log, got %d\", len(logger.errors))\n260: \t}\n261: \n262: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 5*time.Second)\n263: \tdefer cancel()\n264: \ts.Stop(ctx)\n265: \n266: \tselect {\n267: \tcase <-errCh:\n268: \tcase <-time.After(1 * time.Second):\n269: \t}\n270: }\n271: \n272: func TestStartStopLifecycle(t *testing.T) {\n273: \tlistener, err := net.Listen(\"tcp\", \"127.0.0.1:0\")\n274: \tif err != nil {\n275: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"failed to get free port: %v\", err)\n276: \t}\n277: \taddr := listener.Addr().String()\n278: \tlistener.Close()\n279: \n280: \tcfg := Config{\n281: \t\tAddr:            addr,\n282: \t\tReadTimeout:     5 * time.Second,\n283: \t\tWriteTimeout:    5 * time.Second,\n284: \t\tIdleTimeout:     60 * time.Second,\n285: \t\tShutdownTimeout: 5 * time.Second,\n286: \t}\n287: \tlogger := &integrationTestLogger{}\n288: \ts := NewHTTPServer(cfg, logger)\n289: \n290: \terrCh := s.Start()\n291: \tif errCh == nil {\n292: \t\tt.Error(\"Start returned nil error channel\")\n293: \t}\n294: \n295: \ttime.Sleep(100 * time.Millisecond)\n296: \n297: \tctx := context.Background()\n298: \terr = s.Stop(ctx)\n299: \tif err != nil {\n300: \t\tt.Errorf(\"Stop returned error: %v\", err)\n301: \t}\n302: \n303: \tselect {\n304: \tcase <-s.stopCh:\n305: \tcase <-time.After(2 * time.Second):\n306: \t\tt.Error(\"stopCh was not closed after Stop()\")\n307: \t}\n308: \n309: \tselect {\n310: \tcase <-errCh:\n311: \tcase <-time.After(2 * time.Second):\n312: \t}\n313: }\n\n(End of file - total 313 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"net\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"net/http/httptest\"\n\t\"sync\"\n\t\"testing\"\n\t\"time\"\n)\n\ntype integrationTestLogger struct {\n\tmu     sync.Mutex\n\tinfos  []string\n\terrors []string\n}\n\nfunc (l *integrationTestLogger) Info(msg string, args ...any) {","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go","time":{"start":1775901841007,"end":1775901841016}}}}
