{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775902085092,"sessionID":"ses_28401709affeCiPSt6S1RdIOFK","part":{"id":"prt_d7c034f44001Jrznt6wQXee8Tj","messageID":"msg_d7bff96b6001mvyr5iuud20OT1","sessionID":"ses_28401709affeCiPSt6S1RdIOFK","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-8203dde4572b49dba837aed84b9c1a1e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/test/e2e/design.md","content":"# AR-041 — E2E 集成测试\n\n**Module:** test/e2e  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nEnd-to-end integration tests for AgentCube validate the complete system workflow from sandbox creation through code execution, covering all core components: Workload Manager, Router, and PicoD. Tests run against a real Kubernetes cluster (Kind) with full component deployment.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Test Environment\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                          E2E Test Environment (Kind Cluster)                      │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                                  │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n│  │                        Kubernetes Cluster (agentcube-e2e)                    ││\n│  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐    ││\n│  │  │ Workload     │  │   Router     │  │   Redis      │  │   CRDs       │    ││\n│  │  │ Manager      │  │  Deployment  │  │  Deployment  │  │  AgentRuntime│    ││\n│  │  │ Deployment   │  │              │  │              │  │  CodeInterp. │    ││\n│  │  │  (Pod :8080) │  │  (Pod :8080) │  │ (:6379)      │  │              │    ││\n│  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘    ││\n│  │         │                 │                  │                              ││\n│  │         │                 │                  │                              ││\n│  │  ┌──────┴─────────────────┴──────────────────┴──────────────────────────┐  ││\n│  │  │                    Agent Sandbox Pods (created by tests)              │  ││\n│  │  │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │  ││\n│  │  │  │ Sandbox Pod                                                       │ │  ││\n│  │  │  │  ┌────────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐                         │ │  ││\n│  │  │  │  │   PicoD        │  │   Workload     │                         │ │  ││\n│  │  │  │  │   Sidecar      │  │   Container    │                         │ │  ││\n│  │  │  │  │   (:8080)      │  │   (echo agent) │                         │ │  ││\n│  │  │  │  └────────────────┘  └────────────────┘                         │ │  ││\n│  │  │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │  ││\n│  │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  ││\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│\n│                                                                                  │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n│  │                         Port-Forward (localhost)                            ││\n│  │  Workload Manager: localhost:8080 → svc/workloadmanager:8080                ││\n│  │  Router:           localhost:8081 → svc/agentcube-router:8080               ││\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│\n│                                                                                  │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n│  │                         Test Runner                                          ││\n│  │  - Go test framework (testing package)                                       ││\n│  │  - Environment variables: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, ROUTER_URL, API_TOKEN        ││\n│  │  - Python venv for SDK tests                                                 ││\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│\n│                                                                                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\ntest/e2e/\n├── design.md                        # This design document\n├── README.md                        # Test execution guide\n├── run_e2e.sh                       # E2E test orchestration script\n├── kind-config.yaml                 # Kind cluster configuration\n├── e2e_test.go                      # Go E2E test suite entry point\n├── sandbox_test.go                  # Sandbox lifecycle tests\n├── session_test.go                  # Session management tests\n├── code_execution_test.go           # Code execution tests\n├── router_test.go                   # Router invocation tests\n├── idle_cleanup_test.go             # Idle cleanup E2E tests\n├── warm_pool_test.go                # Warm pool tests\n├── fixtures/\n│   ├── echo_agent.yaml              # Echo AgentRuntime fixture\n│   ├── e2e_code_interpreter.yaml    # CodeInterpreter fixture\n│   ├── e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml  # WarmPool fixture\n│   └── test_data/\n│       ├── simple_script.py         # Test Python script\n│       ├── error_script.py          # Error-inducing script\n│       └── large_file.txt           # Large file upload test\n├── framework/\n│   ├── test_context.go              # Test context management\n│   ├── kube_client.go               # Kubernetes client helpers\n│   ├── http_client.go               # HTTP client helpers\n│   ├── wait_helpers.go              # Wait/poll utilities\n│   └── fixture_manager.go           # Fixture loading/cleanup\n├── __init__.py                      # Python test package marker\n└── test_codeinterpreter.py          # Python SDK E2E tests\n```\n\n### Test Flow Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                          E2E Test Execution Flow                                 │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                                  │\n│  1. Setup Phase                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐                   │\n│  │ Kind     │───▶│ Build    │───▶│ Load     │───▶│ Deploy   │                   │\n│  │ Cluster  │    │ Images   │    │ Images   │    │ Helm     │                   │\n│  └──────────┘    └──────────┘    └──────────┘    └──────────┘                   │\n│        │              │              │              │                            │\n│        ▼              ▼              ▼              ▼                            │\n│  ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐                   │\n│  │ Apply    │───▶│ Wait     │───▶│ Port     │───▶│ Setup    │                   │\n│  │ CRDs     │    │ Ready    │    │ Forward  │    │ Auth     │                   │\n│  └──────────┘    └──────────┘    └──────────┘    └──────────┘                   │\n│                                                                                  │\n│  2. Test Execution Phase                                                         │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n│  │  ┌─────────────────────┐                                                     ││\n│  │  │ TestCase-WM-*       │  Workload Manager Tests                            ││\n│  │  │  - Sandbox create   │                                                     ││\n│  │  │  - Sandbox get      │                                                     ││\n│  │  │  - Sandbox delete   │                                                     ││\n│  │  │  - Idempotency      │                                                     ││\n│  │  └─────────────────────┘                                                     ││\n│  │  ┌─────────────────────┐                                                     ││\n│  │  │ TestCase-RT-*       │  Router Tests                                       ││\n│  │  │  - Auth intercept   │                                                     ││\n│  │  │  - Session routing  │                                                     ││\n│  │  │  - Session expiry   │                                                     ││\n│  │  └─────────────────────┘                                                     ││\n│  │  ┌─────────────────────┐                                                     ││\n│  │  │ TestCase-PD-*       │  PicoD Tests                                        ││\n│  │  │  - Python execute   │                                                     ││\n│  │  │  - Error handling   │                                                     ││\n│  │  │  - File operations  │                                                     ││\n│  │  └─────────────────────┘                                                     ││\n│  │  ┌─────────────────────┐                                                     ││\n│  │  │ TestCase-ST-*       │  Store Tests                                        ││\n│  │  │  - Redis Set/Get    │                                                     ││\n│  │  │  - TTL validation   │                                                     ││\n│  │  └─────────────────────┘                                                     ││\n│  │  ┌─────────────────────┐                                                     ││\n│  │  │ TestCase-SDK-*      │  Python SDK Tests                                   ││\n│  │  │  - Context manager  │                                                     ││\n│  │  │  - Exception map    │                                                     ││\n│  │  └─────────────────────┘                                                     ││\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│\n│                                                                                  │\n│  3. Cleanup Phase                                                                │\n│  ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐                                   │\n│  │ Collect  │───▶│ Kill     │───▶│ Delete   │                                   │\n│  │ Logs     │    │ Port-Fwd │    │ Cluster  │                                   │\n│  └──────────┘    └──────────┘    └──────────┘                                   │\n│                                                                                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### TestContext\n\n```go\npackage framework\n\ntype TestContext struct {\n    Namespace           string\n    WorkloadManagerURL  string\n    RouterURL           string\n    APIToken            string\n    K8sClient           *kubernetes.Clientset\n    DynamicClient       dynamic.Interface\n    RESTConfig          *rest.Config\n    AgentCubeClient     versioned.Interface\n    TestID              string\n    StartTime           time.Time\n    CleanupFuncs        []func()\n}\n\nfunc NewTestContext(namespace, wmURL, routerURL, apiToken string) (*TestContext, error) {\n    config, err := rest.InClusterConfig()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get in-cluster config: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    k8sClient, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create k8s client: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    dynamicClient, err := dynamic.NewForConfig(config)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create dynamic client: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    agentCubeClient, err := versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create agentcube client: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    return &TestContext{\n        Namespace:          namespace,\n        WorkloadManagerURL: wmURL,\n        RouterURL:          routerURL,\n        APIToken:           apiToken,\n        K8sClient:          k8sClient,\n        DynamicClient:      dynamicClient,\n        RESTConfig:         config,\n        AgentCubeClient:    agentCubeClient,\n        TestID:             uuid.New().String()[:8],\n        StartTime:          time.Now(),\n        CleanupFuncs:       []func(){},\n    }, nil\n}\n\nfunc (tc *TestContext) AddCleanup(fn func()) {\n    tc.CleanupFuncs = append(tc.CleanupFuncs, fn)\n}\n\nfunc (tc *TestContext) Cleanup() {\n    for i := len(tc.CleanupFuncs) - 1; i >= 0; i-- {\n        tc.CleanupFuncs[i]()\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### SandboxTestClient\n\n```go\npackage framework\n\ntype SandboxTestClient struct {\n    baseURL    string\n    httpClient *http.Client\n    token      string\n}\n\nfunc NewSandboxTestClient(baseURL, token string) *SandboxTestClient {\n    return &SandboxTestClient{\n        baseURL: baseURL,\n        httpClient: &http.Client{\n            Timeout: 30 * time.Second,\n        },\n        token: token,\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (c *SandboxTestClient) CreateSandbox(ctx context.Context, req *types.CreateSandboxRequest) (*types.CreateSandboxResponse, error) {\n    body, err := json.Marshal(req)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to marshal request: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"POST\", c.baseURL+\"/v1/sandbox\", bytes.NewReader(body))\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create request: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    httpReq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    if c.token != \"\" {\n        httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.token)\n    }\n    \n    resp, err := c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to send request: %w\", err)\n    }\n    defer resp.Body.Close()\n    \n    if resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n        respBody, _ := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n        return nil, &APIError{\n            StatusCode: resp.StatusCode,\n            Body:       string(respBody),\n        }\n    }\n    \n    var result types.CreateSandboxResponse\n    if err := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&result); err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to decode response: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    return &result, nil\n}\n\nfunc (c *SandboxTestClient) GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    url := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/v1/sandbox/%s/%s\", c.baseURL, namespace, name)\n    httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"GET\", url, nil)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    \n    if c.token != \"\" {\n        httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.token)\n    }\n    \n    resp, err := c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    defer resp.Body.Close()\n    \n    var result types.SandboxInfo\n    if err := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&result); err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    \n    return &result, nil\n}\n\nfunc (c *SandboxTestClient) DeleteSandbox(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) error {\n    url := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/v1/sandbox/%s/%s\", c.baseURL, namespace, name)\n    httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"DELETE\", url, nil)\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    if c.token != \"\" {\n        httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.token)\n    }\n    \n    resp, err := c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    defer resp.Body.Close()\n    \n    if resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK && resp.StatusCode != http.StatusNoContent {\n        return &APIError{StatusCode: resp.StatusCode}\n    }\n    \n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### RouterTestClient\n\n```go\npackage framework\n\ntype RouterTestClient struct {\n    baseURL    string\n    httpClient *http.Client\n    token      string\n}\n\nfunc NewRouterTestClient(baseURL, token string) *RouterTestClient {\n    return &RouterTestClient{\n        baseURL: baseURL,\n        httpClient: &http.Client{\n            Timeout: 60 * time.Second,\n        },\n        token: token,\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (c *RouterTestClient) InvokeAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name, path string, body []byte) (*http.Response, error) {\n    url := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/v1/namespaces/%s/agent-runtimes/%s/invocations%s\", \n        c.baseURL, namespace, name, path)\n    \n    httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"POST\", url, bytes.NewReader(body))\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    \n    httpReq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    if c.token != \"\" {\n        httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.token)\n    }\n    \n    return c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n}\n\nfunc (c *RouterTestClient) InvokeCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name, sessionID, path string, body []byte) (*http.Response, error) {\n    url := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/v1/namespaces/%s/code-interpreters/%s/invocations%s\",\n        c.baseURL, namespace, name, path)\n    \n    httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"POST\", url, bytes.NewReader(body))\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    \n    httpReq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    httpReq.Header.Set(\"x-agentcube-session-id\", sessionID)\n    if c.token != \"\" {\n        httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.token)\n    }\n    \n    return c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n}\n```\n\n### PicoDTestClient\n\n```go\npackage framework\n\ntype ExecuteRequest struct {\n    Language string `json:\"language\"`\n    Code     string `json:\"code\"`\n}\n\ntype ExecuteResponse struct {\n    Stdout   string `json:\"stdout\"`\n    Stderr   string `json:\"stderr\"`\n    ExitCode int    `json:\"exitCode\"`\n}\n\ntype PicoDTestClient struct {\n    baseURL    string\n    httpClient *http.Client\n    jwtToken   string\n}\n\nfunc NewPicoDTestClient(baseURL, jwtToken string) *PicoDTestClient {\n    return &PicoDTestClient{\n        baseURL: baseURL,\n        httpClient: &http.Client{\n            Timeout: 120 * time.Second,\n        },\n        jwtToken: jwtToken,\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (c *PicoDTestClient) Execute(ctx context.Context, req *ExecuteRequest) (*ExecuteResponse, error) {\n    body, err := json.Marshal(req)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    \n    httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"POST\", c.baseURL+\"/api/execute\", bytes.NewReader(body))\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    \n    httpReq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    if c.jwtToken != \"\" {\n        httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.jwtToken)\n    }\n    \n    resp, err := c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    defer resp.Body.Close()\n    \n    var result ExecuteResponse\n    if err := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&result); err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    \n    return &result, nil\n}\n\nfunc (c *PicoDTestClient) UploadFile(ctx context.Context, filename string, content []byte) error {\n    body := bytes.NewReader(content)\n    httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"POST\", c.baseURL+\"/api/files?path=\"+filename, body)\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    httpReq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/octet-stream\")\n    if c.jwtToken != \"\" {\n        httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.jwtToken)\n    }\n    \n    resp, err := c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    defer resp.Body.Close()\n    \n    if resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"upload failed: %d\", resp.StatusCode)\n    }\n    \n    return nil\n}\n\nfunc (c *PicoDTestClient) ListFiles(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error) {\n    httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"GET\", c.baseURL+\"/api/files\", nil)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    \n    if c.jwtToken != \"\" {\n        httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.jwtToken)\n    }\n    \n    resp, err := c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    defer resp.Body.Close()\n    \n    var result []string\n    if err := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&result); err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    \n    return result, nil\n}\n\nfunc (c *PicoDTestClient) DownloadFile(ctx context.Context, filename string) ([]byte, error) {\n    httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"GET\", c.baseURL+\"/api/files/\"+filename, nil)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    \n    if c.jwtToken != \"\" {\n        httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.jwtToken)\n    }\n    \n    resp, err := c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    defer resp.Body.Close()\n    \n    return io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n}\n```\n\n### APIError\n\n```go\npackage framework\n\ntype APIError struct {\n    StatusCode int\n    Body       string\n}\n\nfunc (e *APIError) Error() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"API error: status=%d body=%s\", e.StatusCode, e.Body)\n}\n\nfunc (e *APIError) IsNotFound() bool {\n    return e.StatusCode == http.StatusNotFound\n}\n\nfunc (e *APIError) IsUnauthorized() bool {\n    return e.StatusCode == http.StatusUnauthorized\n}\n\nfunc (e *APIError) IsBadRequest() bool {\n    return e.StatusCode == http.StatusBadRequest\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Workload Manager API (E2E Tests)\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose | Expected Response |\n|----------|--------|---------|-------------------|\n| `/v1/sandbox` | POST | Create sandbox | `200 OK` + `CreateSandboxResponse` |\n| `/v1/sandbox/:namespace/:name` | GET | Get sandbox info | `200 OK` + `SandboxInfo` |\n| `/v1/sandbox/:namespace/:name` | DELETE | Delete sandbox | `200 OK` or `204 No Content` |\n| `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe | `200 OK` + `{\"status\":\"alive\"}` |\n| `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe | `200 OK` + `{\"status\":\"ready\"}` |\n\n#### CreateSandboxRequest Contract\n\n```json\n{\n    \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime|CodeInterpreter\",\n    \"name\": \"string (required)\",\n    \"namespace\": \"string (required)\"\n}\n```\n\n#### CreateSandboxResponse Contract\n\n```json\n{\n    \"sessionId\": \"string (UUID format)\",\n    \"sandboxId\": \"string (UUID format)\",\n    \"sandboxName\": \"string\",\n    \"entryPoints\": [\n        {\n            \"path\": \"string\",\n            \"protocol\": \"string\",\n            \"endpoint\": \"string (URL)\"\n        }\n    ]\n}\n```\n\n### Router API (E2E Tests)\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose | Expected Response |\n|----------|--------|---------|-------------------|\n| `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe | `200 OK` + `{\"status\":\"alive\"}` |\n| `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe | `200 OK` + `{\"status\":\"ready\"}` |\n| `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Agent invocation proxy | Proxied response or error |\n| `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Code interpreter proxy | Proxied response or error |\n\n#### Invocation Headers\n\n| Header | Required | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|\n| `Authorization` | Yes | Bearer token for auth |\n| `x-agentcube-session-id` | For CI | Session identifier |\n\n### PicoD API (E2E Tests)\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose | Expected Response |\n|----------|--------|---------|-------------------|\n| `/health` | GET | Health check | `200 OK` |\n| `/api/execute` | POST | Execute code | `200 OK` + `ExecuteResponse` |\n| `/api/files` | POST | Upload file | `200 OK` |\n| `/api/files` | GET | List files | `200 OK` + `[\"file1\", ...]` |\n| `/api/files/*path` | GET | Download file | `200 OK` + file content |\n\n#### ExecuteRequest Contract\n\n```json\n{\n    \"language\": \"python|javascript|typescript\",\n    \"code\": \"string (code to execute)\"\n}\n```\n\n#### ExecuteResponse Contract\n\n```json\n{\n    \"stdout\": \"string\",\n    \"stderr\": \"string\",\n    \"exitCode\": \"integer (0 = success)\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Categories in E2E Tests\n\n| Category | HTTP Status | Test Assertion |\n|----------|-------------|----------------|\n| `BadRequest` | 400 | Validate error message contains expected field |\n| `Unauthorized` | 401 | Validate `401` returned without valid token |\n| `NotFound` | 404 | Validate error message contains resource name |\n| `Conflict` | 409 | Used for idempotency validation (same sessionId) |\n| `InternalError` | 500 | Log and fail test with diagnostics |\n| `Timeout` | N/A | Use `WaitFor` with timeout and fail on exceed |\n\n### Test Error Handling Pattern\n\n```go\nfunc handleTestError(t *testing.T, err error, tc *TestContext) {\n    if err == nil {\n        return\n    }\n    \n    var apiErr *APIError\n    if errors.As(err, &apiErr) {\n        t.Logf(\"API Error: status=%d body=%s\", apiErr.StatusCode, apiErr.Body)\n        \n        if apiErr.StatusCode >= 500 {\n            collectComponentLogs(t, tc)\n        }\n    } else {\n        t.Logf(\"Non-API Error: %v\", err)\n    }\n    \n    t.Fail()\n}\n\nfunc collectComponentLogs(t *testing.T, tc *TestContext) {\n    components := []string{\"workloadmanager\", \"router\"}\n    for _, comp := range components {\n        logs, err := tc.K8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(tc.Namespace).\n            GetLogs(comp, &corev1.PodLogOptions{TailLines: pointer.Int64(100)}).\n            DoRaw(context.Background())\n        if err == nil {\n            t.Logf(\"=== %s logs ===\\n%s\", comp, logs)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Retry Pattern for Flaky Operations\n\n```go\nfunc RetryWithBackoff(ctx context.Context, op func() error, maxAttempts int, baseDelay time.Duration) error {\n    var lastErr error\n    for attempt := 0; attempt < maxAttempts; attempt++ {\n        err := op()\n        if err == nil {\n            return nil\n        }\n        lastErr = err\n        \n        if !isRetryable(err) {\n            return err\n        }\n        \n        delay := baseDelay * time.Duration(1<<attempt)\n        select {\n        case <-ctx.Done():\n            return ctx.Err()\n        case <-time.After(delay):\n        }\n    }\n    return fmt.Errorf(\"max attempts exceeded: %w\", lastErr)\n}\n\nfunc isRetryable(err error) bool {\n    var apiErr *APIError\n    if errors.As(err, &apiErr) {\n        return apiErr.StatusCode >= 500 || apiErr.StatusCode == 429\n    }\n    return true\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Test Categories\n\n| Category | Coverage | Duration |\n|----------|----------|----------|\n| Workload Manager | Sandbox CRUD, idempotency, warm pool | ~2 min |\n| Router | Auth, session routing, proxy | ~3 min |\n| PicoD | Execute, files, auth | ~2 min |\n| Store | Redis operations, TTL | ~1 min |\n| Integration | Full workflow end-to-end | ~5 min |\n| Python SDK | Client lifecycle, exceptions | ~2 min |\n\n### TestCase-WM-001: Sandbox Creation\n\n```go\nfunc TestSandboxCreate(t *testing.T) {\n    tc := setupTestContext(t)\n    defer tc.Cleanup()\n    \n    client := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n    \n    req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n        Kind:      types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n        Name:      \"e2e-code-interpreter\",\n        Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n    }\n    \n    ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n    defer cancel()\n    \n    resp, err := client.CreateSandbox(ctx, req)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    assert.NotEmpty(t, resp.SessionID, \"sessionId should not be empty\")\n    assert.NotEmpty(t, resp.SandboxID, \"sandboxId should not be empty\")\n    assert.Len(t, resp.EntryPoints, 1, \"should have at least one entry point\")\n    \n    tc.AddCleanup(func() {\n        client.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), tc.Namespace, resp.SandboxName)\n    })\n    \n    assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n        pod, err := tc.K8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(tc.Namespace).\n            Get(context.Background(), resp.SandboxName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n        if err != nil {\n            return false\n        }\n        return pod.Status.Phase == corev1.PodRunning\n    }, 60*time.Second, 2*time.Second, \"sandbox pod should become running\")\n}\n```\n\n### TestCase-WM-002: Idempotency\n\n```go\nfunc TestSandboxIdempotency(t *testing.T) {\n    tc := setupTestContext(t)\n    defer tc.Cleanup()\n    \n    client := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n    \n    req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n        Kind:      types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n        Name:      \"e2e-code-interpreter-idempotent\",\n        Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n    }\n    \n    ctx := context.Background()\n    \n    resp1, err := client.CreateSandbox(ctx, req)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    tc.AddCleanup(func() {\n        client.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), tc.Namespace, resp1.SandboxName)\n    })\n    \n    resp2, err := client.CreateSandbox(ctx, req)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    assert.Equal(t, resp1.SessionID, resp2.SessionID, \n        \"same name should return same sessionId\")\n    assert.Equal(t, resp1.SandboxID, resp2.SandboxID,\n        \"same name should return same sandboxId\")\n}\n```\n\n### TestCase-WM-003: Invalid Input\n\n```go\nfunc TestSandboxInvalidInput(t *testing.T) {\n    tc := setupTestContext(t)\n    defer tc.Cleanup()\n    \n    client := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n    \n    tests := []struct {\n        name    string\n        request *types.CreateSandboxRequest\n        expect  int\n    }{\n        {\n            name: \"missing name\",\n            request: &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n                Kind:      types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n                Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n            },\n            expect: http.StatusBadRequest,\n        },\n        {\n            name: \"missing namespace\",\n            request: &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n                Kind: types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n                Name: \"test-sandbox\",\n            },\n            expect: http.StatusBadRequest,\n        },\n        {\n            name: \"invalid kind\",\n            request: &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n                Kind:      \"InvalidKind\",\n                Name:      \"test-sandbox\",\n                Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n            },\n            expect: http.StatusBadRequest,\n        },\n    }\n    \n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            ctx := context.Background()\n            _, err := client.CreateSandbox(ctx, tt.request)\n            \n            var apiErr *APIError\n            require.Error(t, err)\n            require.True(t, errors.As(err, &apiErr))\n            assert.Equal(t, tt.expect, apiErr.StatusCode)\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### TestCase-RT-001: Auth Intercept\n\n```go\nfunc TestRouterAuthIntercept(t *testing.T) {\n    tc := setupTestContext(t)\n    defer tc.Cleanup()\n    \n    tests := []struct {\n        name    string\n        token   string\n        expect  int\n    }{\n        {\n            name:   \"no token\",\n            token:  \"\",\n            expect: http.StatusUnauthorized,\n        },\n        {\n            name:   \"invalid token\",\n            token:  \"invalid-token\",\n            expect: http.StatusUnauthorized,\n        },\n        {\n            name:   \"valid token\",\n            token:  tc.APIToken,\n            expect: http.StatusOK,\n        },\n    }\n    \n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            client := NewRouterTestClient(tc.RouterURL, tt.token)\n            \n            ctx := context.Background()\n            resp, err := client.InvokeAgentRuntime(ctx, tc.Namespace, \"echo-agent\", \"/\", []byte(\"{}\"))\n            require.NoError(t, err)\n            defer resp.Body.Close()\n            \n            assert.Equal(t, tt.expect, resp.StatusCode)\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### TestCase-RT-002: Session Routing\n\n```go\nfunc TestRouterSessionRouting(t *testing.T) {\n    tc := setupTestContext(t)\n    defer tc.Cleanup()\n    \n    wmClient := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n    \n    req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n        Kind:      types.AgentRuntimeKind,\n        Name:      \"echo-agent\",\n        Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n    }\n    \n    sandbox, err := wmClient.CreateSandbox(context.Background(), req)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    tc.AddCleanup(func() {\n        wmClient.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), tc.Namespace, sandbox.SandboxName)\n    })\n    \n    routerClient := NewRouterTestClient(tc.RouterURL, tc.APIToken)\n    \n    ctx := context.Background()\n    resp, err := routerClient.InvokeAgentRuntime(ctx, tc.Namespace, \"echo-agent\", \"/echo\", \n        []byte(`{\"message\": \"hello e2e\"}`))\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    defer resp.Body.Close()\n    \n    assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, resp.StatusCode)\n    \n    body, err := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Contains(t, string(body), \"hello e2e\")\n}\n```\n\n### TestCase-RT-003: Session Expiry\n\n```go\nfunc TestRouterSessionExpiry(t *testing.T) {\n    tc := setupTestContext(t)\n    defer tc.Cleanup()\n    \n    wmClient := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n    \n    req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n        Kind:      types.AgentRuntimeKind,\n        Name:      \"echo-agent-short-ttl\",\n        Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n    }\n    \n    sandbox, err := wmClient.CreateSandbox(context.Background(), req)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    tc.AddCleanup(func() {\n        wmClient.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), tc.Namespace, sandbox.SandboxName)\n    })\n    \n    routerClient := NewRouterTestClient(tc.RouterURL, tc.APIToken)\n    \n    ctx := context.Background()\n    \n    time.Sleep(35 * time.Second)\n    \n    resp, err := routerClient.InvokeAgentRuntime(ctx, tc.Namespace, \"echo-agent-short-ttl\", \"/\", nil)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    defer resp.Body.Close()\n    \n    assert.Equal(t, http.StatusNotFound, resp.StatusCode)\n}\n```\n\n### TestCase-ST-001: Redis Set/Get\n\n```go\nfunc TestStoreRedisSetGet(t *testing.T) {\n    tc := setupTestContext(t)\n    defer tc.Cleanup()\n    \n    redisClient := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n        Addr: fmt.Sprintf(\"redis.%s.svc.cluster.local:6379\", tc.Namespace),\n    })\n    \n    sessionInfo := &types.SandboxInfo{\n        SessionID:        uuid.New().String(),\n        SandboxID:        uuid.New().String(),\n        SandboxName:      \"test-sandbox\",\n        SandboxNamespace: tc.Namespace,\n        CreatedAt:        time.Now(),\n        ExpiresAt:        time.Now().Add(24 * time.Hour),\n    }\n    \n    key := fmt.Sprintf(\"session:%s\", sessionInfo.SessionID)\n    value, err := json.Marshal(sessionInfo)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    ctx := context.Background()\n    err = redisClient.Set(ctx, key, value, 24*time.Hour).Err()\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    result, err := redisClient.Get(ctx, key).Result()\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    var retrieved types.SandboxInfo\n    err = json.Unmarshal([]byte(result), &retrieved)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    assert.Equal(t, sessionInfo.SessionID, retrieved.SessionID)\n    assert.Equal(t, sessionInfo.SandboxName, retrieved.SandboxName)\n}\n```\n\n### TestCase-ST-002: TTL Validation\n\n```go\nfunc TestStoreTTLValidation(t *testing.T) {\n    tc := setupTestContext(t)\n    defer tc.Cleanup()\n    \n    redisClient := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n        Addr: fmt.Sprintf(\"redis.%s.svc.cluster.local:6379\", tc.Namespace),\n    })\n    \n    sessionID := uuid.New().String()\n    key := fmt.Sprintf(\"session:%s\", sessionID)\n    \n    ctx := context.Background()\n    err := redisClient.Set(ctx, key, \"test-value\", 24*time.Hour).Err()\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    ttl, err := redisClient.TTL(ctx, key).Result()\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    assert.GreaterOrEqual(t, ttl.Seconds(), float64(23*time.Hour/1e9))\n    assert.LessOrEqual(t, ttl.Seconds(), float64(24*time.Hour/1e9))\n}\n```\n\n### TestCase-PD-001: Python Execute\n\n```go\nfunc TestPicoDPythonExecute(t *testing.T) {\n    tc := setupTestContext(t)\n    defer tc.Cleanup()\n    \n    wmClient := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n    \n    req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n        Kind:      types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n        Name:      \"e2e-code-interpreter\",\n        Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n    }\n    \n    sandbox, err := wmClient.CreateSandbox(context.Background(), req)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    tc.AddCleanup(func() {\n        wmClient.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), tc.Namespace, sandbox.SandboxName)\n    })\n    \n    waitForPodRunning(t, tc, sandbox.SandboxName)\n    \n    jwtToken := getJWTFromRouter(t, tc.RouterURL, tc.APIToken, sandbox.SessionID)\n    picodURL := fmt.Sprintf(\"http://%s.%s.pod.cluster.local:8080\", \n        sandbox.SandboxName, tc.Namespace)\n    \n    picodClient := NewPicoDTestClient(picodURL, jwtToken)\n    \n    ctx := context.Background()\n    execResp, err := picodClient.Execute(ctx, &ExecuteRequest{\n        Language: \"python\",\n        Code:     `print(\"hello\")`,\n    })\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    assert.Equal(t, \"hello\\n\", execResp.Stdout)\n    assert.Equal(t, 0, execResp.ExitCode)\n    assert.Empty(t, execResp.Stderr)\n}\n```\n\n### TestCase-PD-002: Error Handling\n\n```go\nfunc TestPicoDErrorHandling(t *testing.T) {\n    tc := setupTestContext(t)\n    defer tc.Cleanup()\n    \n    wmClient := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n    \n    req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n        Kind:      types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n        Name:      \"e2e-code-interpreter\",\n        Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n    }\n    \n    sandbox, err := wmClient.CreateSandbox(context.Background(), req)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    tc.AddCleanup(func() {\n        wmClient.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), tc.Namespace, sandbox.SandboxName)\n    })\n    \n    waitForPodRunning(t, tc, sandbox.SandboxName)\n    \n    jwtToken := getJWTFromRouter(t, tc.RouterURL, tc.APIToken, sandbox.SessionID)\n    picodURL := fmt.Sprintf(\"http://%s.%s.pod.cluster.local:8080\", \n        sandbox.SandboxName, tc.Namespace)\n    \n    picodClient := NewPicoDTestClient(picodURL, jwtToken)\n    \n    ctx := context.Background()\n    execResp, err := picodClient.Execute(ctx, &ExecuteRequest{\n        Language: \"python\",\n        Code:     `import syntax_error`,\n    })\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    assert.NotEqual(t, 0, execResp.ExitCode)\n    assert.Contains(t, execResp.Stderr, \"SyntaxError\")\n}\n```\n\n### TestCase-SDK-001: Context Manager\n\n```go\nfunc TestSDKContextManager(t *testing.T) {\n    if testing.Short() {\n        t.Skip(\"skipping SDK test in short mode\")\n    }\n    \n    venvDir := os.Getenv(\"E2E_VENV_DIR\")\n    if venvDir == \"\" {\n        venvDir = \"/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv\"\n    }\n    \n    pythonCmd := filepath.Join(venvDir, \"bin\", \"python\")\n    \n    code := `\nimport agentcube\nimport sys\n\ncreated_session_id = None\n\nwith agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient(\n    workload_manager_url=\"${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}\",\n    router_url=\"${ROUTER_URL}\",\n    api_token=\"${API_TOKEN}\",\n    namespace=\"${NAMESPACE}\"\n) as client:\n    created_session_id = client.session_id\n    print(f\"Session created: {created_session_id}\")\n    \n    result = client.execute(language=\"python\", code=\"print('test')\")\n    print(f\"Execution result: {result.stdout}\")\n\nprint(\"Context closed\")\n\nsys.exit(0)\n`\n    \n    envVars := fmt.Sprintf(`WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=%s ROUTER_URL=%s API_TOKEN=%s NAMESPACE=%s`,\n        os.Getenv(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"),\n        os.Getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\"),\n        os.Getenv(\"API_TOKEN\"),\n        os.Getenv(\"AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\"))\n    \n    cmd := exec.CommandContext(context.Background(), pythonCmd, \"-c\", code)\n    cmd.Env = append(os.Environ(), strings.Split(envVars, \" \")...)\n    \n    output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n    require.NoError(t, err, \"Python output: %s\", output)\n    \n    assert.Contains(t, string(output), \"Session created:\")\n    assert.Contains(t, string(output), \"Context closed\")\n}\n```\n\n### TestCase-SDK-002: Exception Mapping\n\n```go\nfunc TestSDKExceptionMapping(t *testing.T) {\n    if testing.Short() {\n        t.Skip(\"skipping SDK test in short mode\")\n    }\n    \n    venvDir := os.Getenv(\"E2E_VENV_DIR\")\n    if venvDir == \"\" {\n        venvDir = \"/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv\"\n    }\n    \n    pythonCmd := filepath.Join(venvDir, \"bin\", \"python\")\n    \n    code := `\nimport agentcube\nimport sys\n\ntry:\n    client = agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient(\n        workload_manager_url=\"${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}\",\n        router_url=\"${ROUTER_URL}\",\n        api_token=\"invalid-token\",\n        namespace=\"${NAMESPACE}\"\n    )\n    client.execute(language=\"python\", code=\"print('test')\")\nexcept agentcube.AgentCubeError as e:\n    print(f\"Caught AgentCubeError: {type(e).__name__}\")\n    print(f\"Message: {e.message}\")\n    sys.exit(0)\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"Caught unexpected exception: {type(e).__name__}: {e}\")\n    sys.exit(1)\n\nsys.exit(1)\n`\n    \n    envVars := fmt.Sprintf(`WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=%s ROUTER_URL=%s NAMESPACE=%s`,\n        os.Getenv(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"),\n        os.Getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\"),\n        os.Getenv(\"AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\"))\n    \n    cmd := exec.CommandContext(context.Background(), pythonCmd, \"-c\", code)\n    cmd.Env = append(os.Environ(), strings.Split(envVars, \" \")...)\n    \n    output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n    require.NoError(t, err, \"Python output: %s\", output)\n    \n    assert.Contains(t, string(output), \"Caught AgentCubeError\")\n}\n```\n\n### Warm Pool Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestWarmPoolCreation(t *testing.T) {\n    tc := setupTestContext(t)\n    defer tc.Cleanup()\n    \n    applyFixture(t, tc, \"fixtures/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml\")\n    \n    assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n        pods, err := tc.K8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(\"default\").\n            List(context.Background(), metav1.ListOptions{\n                LabelSelector: \"agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool=e2e-code-interpreter-warmpool\",\n            })\n        if err != nil {\n            return false\n        }\n        return len(pods.Items) >= 2\n    }, 60*time.Second, 2*time.Second, \"warm pool should have 2 ready pods\")\n    \n    wmClient := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n    \n    startTime := time.Now()\n    req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n        Kind:      types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n        Name:      \"e2e-code-interpreter-warmpool\",\n        Namespace: \"default\",\n    }\n    \n    resp, err := wmClient.CreateSandbox(context.Background(), req)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    allocationTime := time.Since(startTime)\n    assert.Less(t, allocationTime.Seconds(), 5.0, \n        \"warm pool allocation should be fast (<5s)\")\n    \n    tc.AddCleanup(func() {\n        wmClient.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), \"default\", resp.SandboxName)\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### Idle Cleanup E2E Test\n\n```go\nfunc TestIdleCleanupE2E(t *testing.T) {\n    tc := setupTestContext(t)\n    defer tc.Cleanup()\n    \n    wmClient := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n    \n    req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n        Kind:      types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n        Name:      \"e2e-code-interpreter-idle\",\n        Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n    }\n    \n    sandbox, err := wmClient.CreateSandbox(context.Background(), req)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    waitForPodRunning(t, tc, sandbox.SandboxName)\n    \n    time.Sleep(16 * time.Minute)\n    \n    assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n        _, err := tc.K8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(tc.Namespace).\n            Get(context.Background(), sandbox.SandboxName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n        return apierrors.IsNotFound(err)\n    }, 5*time.Minute, 10*time.Second, \"idle sandbox should be cleaned up\")\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Test Execution\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Description |\n|----------|----------|-------------|\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Yes | Workload Manager endpoint (e.g., `http://localhost:8080`) |\n| `ROUTER_URL` | Yes | Router endpoint (e.g., `http://localhost:8081`) |\n| `API_TOKEN` | Yes | Kubernetes service account token |\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | Yes | Namespace for test resources (default: `agentcube`) |\n| `E2E_VENV_DIR` | No | Python venv directory for SDK tests |\n| `E2E_SKIP_SETUP` | No | Skip cluster setup if `true` |\n| `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER` | No | Clean cluster before/after tests |\n\n### Test Runner Script\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nE2E_CLUSTER_NAME=\"${E2E_CLUSTER_NAME:-agentcube-e2e}\"\nWORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT=\"${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT:-8080}\"\nROUTER_LOCAL_PORT=\"${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT:-8081}\"\nAGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=\"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE:-agentcube}\"\n\ncleanup() {\n    kill $PORT_FORWARD_WM_PID $PORT_FORWARD_ROUTER_PID || true\n    kind delete cluster --name \"$E2E_CLUSTER_NAME\" || true\n}\n\ntrap cleanup EXIT\n\ngo test -v ./test/e2e/... \\\n    -timeout 30m \\\n    -count=1 \\\n    -workload-manager-url=\"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n    -router-url=\"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n    -api-token=\"$API_TOKEN\" \\\n    -namespace=\"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\"\n```\n\n### Go Test Flags\n\n```go\nvar (\n    workloadManagerURL = flag.String(\"workload-manager-url\", \"\", \"Workload Manager URL\")\n    routerURL          = flag.String(\"router-url\", \"\", \"Router URL\")\n    apiToken           = flag.String(\"api-token\", \"\", \"API token for authentication\")\n    namespace          = flag.String(\"namespace\", \"agentcube\", \"Test namespace\")\n)\n\nfunc TestMain(m *testing.M) {\n    flag.Parse()\n    \n    if *workloadManagerURL == \"\" || *routerURL == \"\" || *apiToken == \"\" {\n        fmt.Println(\"Required flags: -workload-manager-url, -router-url, -api-token\")\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n    \n    os.Exit(m.Run())\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Wait Helpers\n\n```go\npackage framework\n\nfunc WaitForPodRunning(t *testing.T, tc *TestContext, podName string) {\n    assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n        pod, err := tc.K8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(tc.Namespace).\n            Get(context.Background(), podName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n        if err != nil {\n            return false\n        }\n        return pod.Status.Phase == corev1.PodRunning\n    }, 120*time.Second, 2*time.Second)\n}\n\nfunc WaitForPodDeleted(t *testing.T, tc *TestContext, podName string) {\n    assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n        _, err := tc.K8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(tc.Namespace).\n            Get(context.Background(), podName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n        return apierrors.IsNotFound(err)\n    }, 60*time.Second, 2*time.Second)\n}\n\nfunc WaitForSandboxReady(t *testing.T, tc *TestContext, sandboxName string) {\n    assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n        sandbox, err := tc.AgentCubeClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().\n            Sandboxes(tc.Namespace).\n            Get(context.Background(), sandboxName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n        if err != nil {\n            return false\n        }\n        return sandbox.Status.Phase == \"Ready\"\n    }, 120*time.Second, 2*time.Second)\n}\n\nfunc WaitForServiceEndpoint(t *testing.T, baseURL string) {\n    assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n        client := &http.Client{Timeout: 2 * time.Second}\n        resp, err := client.Get(baseURL + \"/health\")\n        if err != nil {\n            return false\n        }\n        defer resp.Body.Close()\n        return resp.StatusCode == http.StatusOK\n    }, 30*time.Second, 500*time.Millisecond)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.31.0 | Kubernetes API client |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | local | AgentCube typed client |\n| `github.com/stretchr/testify` | v1.9.0 | Test assertions |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.6.0 | UUID generation |\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.18.0 | Redis client for store tests |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.19.0 | Controller test utilities |\n\n---\n\n## Kind Cluster Configuration\n\n```yaml\nkind: Cluster\napiVersion: kind.x-k8s.io/v1alpha4\nname: agentcube-e2e\nnodes:\n  - role: control-plane\n    kubeadmConfigPatches:\n      - |\n        kind: InitConfiguration\n        nodeRegistration:\n          kubeletExtraArgs:\n            node-labels: \"ingress-ready=true\"\n    extraPortMappings:\n      - containerPort: 80\n        hostPort: 80\n        protocol: TCP\n      - containerPort: 443\n        hostPort: 443\n        protocol: TCP\n  - role: worker\n  - role: worker\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [x] `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` - E2E test orchestration script\n- [x] `test/e2e/kind-config.yaml` - Kind cluster configuration\n- [ ] `test/e2e/e2e_test.go` - Go E2E test suite entry point\n- [ ] `test/e2e/sandbox_test.go` - Sandbox lifecycle tests (WM-001, WM-002, WM-003)\n- [ ] `test/e2e/session_test.go` - Session management tests\n- [ ] `test/e2e/code_execution_test.go` - Code execution tests (PD-001, PD-002)\n- [ ] `test/e2e/router_test.go` - Router invocation tests (RT-001, RT-002, RT-003)\n- [ ] `test/e2e/store_test.go` - Store tests (ST-001, ST-002)\n- [ ] `test/e2e/idle_cleanup_test.go` - Idle cleanup E2E tests\n- [ ] `test/e2e/warm_pool_test.go` - Warm pool tests\n- [ ] `test/e2e/framework/test_context.go` - Test context management\n- [ ] `test/e2e/framework/kube_client.go` - Kubernetes client helpers\n- [ ] `test/e2e/framework/http_client.go` - HTTP client helpers\n- [ ] `test/e2e/framework/wait_helpers.go` - Wait/poll utilities\n- [ ] `test/e2e/framework/fixture_manager.go` - Fixture loading/cleanup\n- [ ] `test/e2e/fixtures/echo_agent.yaml` - Echo AgentRuntime fixture\n- [ ] `test/e2e/fixtures/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` - CodeInterpreter fixture\n- [ ] `test/e2e/fixtures/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` - WarmPool fixture\n- [ ] `test/e2e/test_codeinterpreter.py` - Python SDK E2E tests (SDK-001, SDK-002)\n\n---\n\n## CI Integration\n\n### GitHub Actions Workflow (`.github/workflows/e2e.yml`)\n\n```yaml\nname: Agentcube E2E Tests\non:\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main, release-*]\n  \njobs:\n  e2e-test:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      \n      - uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n        with:\n          go-version: '1.24'\n      \n      - uses: helm/kind-action@v1\n        with:\n          install_only: true\n          version: v0.30.0\n          cluster_name: agentcube-e2e\n      \n      - name: Run E2E tests\n        env:\n          ARTIFACTS_PATH: ${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs\n        run: make e2e\n      \n      - name: Upload logs on failure\n        if: failure()\n        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n        with:\n          name: e2e-logs\n          path: e2e-logs/\n      \n      - name: Cleanup\n        if: always()\n        run: make e2e-clean\n```\n\n---\n\n## Metrics and Observability\n\n### Test Metrics\n\n| Metric | Collection Method |\n|--------|-------------------|\n| Test duration | Go test `-v` output timestamp |\n| Pod creation time | Time from CreateSandbox to PodRunning |\n| Warm pool allocation time | Time from request to response |\n| Execution latency | Time from execute request to response |\n| Cleanup effectiveness | Pods deleted after idle timeout |\n\n### Test Report Format\n\n```\n=== E2E Test Report ===\nDate: 2026-04-11\nCluster: agentcube-e2e (Kind v0.30.0)\nNamespace: agentcube\n\nTest Suite              | Pass | Fail | Skip | Duration\n------------------------|------|------|------|----------\nWorkload Manager        | 5    | 0    | 0    | 2m15s\nRouter                  | 4    | 0    | 0    | 3m10s\nPicoD                   | 6    | 0    | 0    | 2m30s\nStore                   | 2    | 0    | 0    | 1m05s\nWarm Pool               | 2    | 0    | 0    | 3m45s\nIdle Cleanup            | 1    | 0    | 0    | 16m10s\nPython SDK              | 2    | 0    | 0    | 2m20s\n------------------------|------|------|------|----------\nTotal                   | 22   | 0    | 0    | 30m35s\n\nComponent Health:\n- Workload Manager: OK (p50=2.1s creation time)\n- Router: OK (p50=15ms routing latency)\n- Redis: OK (TTL validated)\n- Warm Pool: OK (2 pods ready, allocation <5s)\n```"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/agentd/main.go\">\nERROR [8:2] \"time\" imported and not used\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/test/e2e/run_e2e.sh":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/test/e2e/kind-config.yaml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/manifests/charts/base/values.yaml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z